title: Advisory Committee on Mental Health established
content_text: Chaired by Mr Wong Yan-lung, SC, the new committee will advise the Government on mental health policies, including the establishment of more integral and comprehensive approaches to tackle multi-faceted mental health issues in Hong Kong. It will assist the Government in developing policies, strategies and measures to enhance mental health services in Hong Kong. It will follow up on and monitor the implementation of the recommendations of the 2017 Mental Health Review Report. Welcoming the new committee on board, the Secretary for Food and Health, Professor Sophia Chan, said, "I am deeply touched by and most grateful for the readiness and commitment of all new appointees

"I am deeply touched by and most grateful for the readiness and commitment of all new appointees to serve." The first term of the Advisory Committee on Mental Health will run for a period of two years from December 1, 2017, to November 30, 2019. "As the World Health Organization puts it, there is no health without mental health. Striving to improve the mental health of specific sectors within the community, including children and adolescents, adults and the elderly, is ever more challenging. It calls for leadership, determination and cross-sectoral collaboration. "I extend my warm wishes to the Advisory Committee and look

determination and cross-sectoral collaboration. "I extend my warm wishes to the Advisory Committee and look forward to early improvements being introduced for the mental health services in Hong Kong." The Advisory Committee on Mental Health comprises members from various sectors with a great wealth of expertise and experience including professionals from the healthcare, social service and education sectors, representatives from patient and carer advocacy groups, and lay persons with interest in mental health.
